# Software Engineer - Back End Development

**Department:** Engineering
**Reports To:** Lead Software Engineer
**Location:** Sydney, NSW
**Status:** Full-time

## Company Overview
Our company is a fast-growing technology firm specializing in cloud-based solutions for enterprise customers. Founded in 2015, we've grown to over 200 employees globally and serve clients in finance, healthcare, and retail sectors.

## Position Summary
We are looking for an experienced Software Engineer to join our back-end development team. The ideal candidate will design, develop, and maintain efficient, reusable, and reliable server-side code for our cloud platform. You will collaborate with front-end developers and other team members to establish objectives and design cohesive, scalable solutions.

## Key Responsibilities
* Design and implement robust, scalable, and secure server-side applications using Python, Go, and related technologies
* Write clean, maintainable code with comprehensive test coverage
* Collaborate with front-end developers to integrate user-facing elements with server-side logic
* Optimize applications for maximum speed and scalability
* Implement security and data protection measures
* Debug production issues and implement fixes
* Participate in code reviews and provide constructive feedback to other developers
* Maintain and improve existing codebases and peer review code changes
* Stay informed of emerging technologies and industry trends

## Required Qualifications
* Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field (or equivalent practical experience)
* 3+ years of professional experience in software development
* Strong proficiency in Python and/or Go
* Experience with RESTful APIs and microservices architecture
* Solid understanding of database technologies (SQL and NoSQL)
* Familiarity with cloud services (AWS, GCP, or Azure)
* Experience with version control systems (Git)
* Understanding of fundamental design principles for building scalable applications
* Knowledge of security principles and best practices
* Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills

## Preferred Qualifications
* Experience with container technologies (Docker, Kubernetes)
* Understanding of CI/CD pipelines
* Knowledge of message queuing systems (Kafka, RabbitMQ)
* Experience with monitoring and logging tools
* Contributions to open-source projects
* Experience mentoring junior developers

## Benefits
* Competitive salary package with stock options
* Health, dental, and vision insurance
* 20 days annual leave plus public holidays
* Flexible working arrangements
* Professional development budget
* Regular team events and activities
* Modern office with snacks and beverages

